---
import Layout from '../components/Layout.astro';
import Frame from '../components/Frame.astro';
import GateBadge from '../components/GateBadge.astro';
import Publisher from '../components/Publisher.astro';
import { listSeeds, seedGenreVersion } from '../lib/seeds.ts';
import { formatDate } from '../lib/corpus.ts';
import { WEBSITE_ID } from '../lib/site.ts';
import PageActionBar from '../components/PageActionBar.astro';

// The seed storefront — the sibling of recipes.astro. Every seed in the corpus, as a card that
// links to its nested detail page (/seeds/<slug>.html). The list is generated from the corpus at
// build, so publishing a seed (a new `.md` under seeds/) adds a card and a page with no edit here.
// The corpus ships the canonical `sporo` seed; the empty-state branch below is kept as a genuine
// fallback (it teaches what a seed is and where trust comes from) for a build where none exist.
const seeds = listSeeds()
  .map(({ slug, meta, summary, sealed }) => ({
    slug,
    version: meta.version ?? '',
    title: meta.title ?? slug,
    headline: (meta.title ?? slug).split(' — ')[0],
    target: meta.target ?? '',
    summary,
    date: formatDate(meta.date),
    sealed,
  }))
  .sort((a, b) => a.title.localeCompare(b.title));

const genreVersion = seedGenreVersion();

const head = {
  title: 'sporo — the seed corpus',
  description:
    'Every transferable install seed in the sporo corpus: real, gate-checked, versioned seeds an AI agent can use to bring one named tool into a repository that has never had it.',
  path: '/seeds.html',
  mdMirror: 'seeds.md',
  og: {
    type: 'website' as const,
    title: 'sporo seeds — the corpus',
    description:
      'Real, gate-checked, versioned install seeds an AI agent uses to bring one named tool into a repository that has never had it.',
  },
  twitter: {},
  jsonLd: {
    '@type': 'CollectionPage',
    name: 'sporo seeds',
    url: 'https://sporo.dev/seeds.html',
    description: 'The sporo seed corpus — transferable installs that bring one named tool into a repository.',
    isPartOf: { '@id': WEBSITE_ID },
    inLanguage: 'en',
    mainEntity: {
      '@type': 'ItemList',
      itemListElement: seeds.map((s, i) => ({
        '@type': 'ListItem',
        position: i + 1,
        url: `https://sporo.dev/seeds/${s.slug}.html`,
        name: s.headline,
      })),
    },
  },
};
---

<Layout head={head} active="seeds">
  <Frame layout="wide">
    <section style="position:relative;padding:clamp(4rem,9vh,7rem) clamp(1.25rem,3vw,2.5rem) 3rem;overflow:clip">
      <div aria-hidden="true" style="position:absolute;top:1.5rem;right:clamp(1rem,2.5vw,2rem);font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',ui-monospace,monospace;font-weight:600;font-size:clamp(5rem,11vw,9rem);line-height:1;color:var(--ghost);pointer-events:none;user-select:none">✦</div>
      <PageActionBar title="The sporo seed corpus" path="/seeds.html" mdUrl="seeds.md">
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:1rem;font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',ui-monospace,monospace;font-size:.74rem;letter-spacing:.16em;text-transform:uppercase"><span style="color:var(--accent);font-weight:600">◉</span><span style="flex:0 0 3.5rem;height:1px;background:var(--line)"></span><span style="color:var(--muted)">the corpus</span></div>
      </PageActionBar>
      <h1 style="font-size:clamp(2.4rem,6vw,4rem);line-height:1.02;letter-spacing:-.045em;font-weight:760;max-width:16ch;text-wrap:balance">Seeds, ready to plant.</h1>
      <p style="margin-top:1.4rem;max-width:58ch;color:var(--muted);font-size:clamp(1.02rem,1.7vw,1.2rem);text-wrap:pretty">Each seed brings one named tool into a repository that has never had it — detect whether it is already there, install it from an origin the seed vouches for, prove it runs, put it to use, and account for every move. New to the idea? <a href="what-is-a-seed.html" style="text-decoration:underline;text-underline-offset:3px">What a seed is →</a></p>
      <p style="margin-top:1rem;max-width:58ch;color:var(--muted);font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',ui-monospace,monospace;font-size:.78rem;line-height:1.6;text-wrap:pretty">Every seed here is sealed — its bytes hash (sha256) to a value committed in the public registry — and gate-passed against the seed genre (v{genreVersion}), re-checked on every push. Its exported bytes are also <strong>attested</strong> — Sigstore-signed to the pipeline, so you can prove offline the file you hold came through here unchanged (<code style="font-size:.92em">gh attestation verify &lt;seed&gt;.md -R ydnikolaev/sporo</code>). <a href="https://github.com/ydnikolaev/sporo/actions/workflows/ci.yml" style="color:var(--accent);text-decoration:underline;text-underline-offset:3px">Verified in CI ↗</a></p>

      {seeds.length > 0 ? (
        <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fill,minmax(300px,400px));justify-content:start;gap:1rem;margin-top:3.2rem">
          {seeds.map((s) => (
            <a
              href={`seeds/${s.slug}.html`}
              class="seed-card"
              style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:1rem;background:var(--card);padding:1.5rem 1.5rem 1.3rem;text-decoration:none;color:inherit;transition:border-color .18s ease,transform .18s ease"
            >
              <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:.5rem;margin-bottom:.9rem;font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',ui-monospace,monospace;font-size:.72rem;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase">
                <span style="color:var(--accent);font-weight:600">v{s.version}</span>
                {s.date && <span style="color:var(--muted)">{s.date}</span>}
              </div>
              <h2 title={s.title} style="font-size:1.25rem;line-height:1.18;letter-spacing:-.02em;font-weight:680;color:var(--ink)">{s.headline}</h2>
              {s.target && <div style="margin-top:.5rem;font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',ui-monospace,monospace;font-size:.72rem;color:var(--accent)">{s.target}</div>}
              <p style="margin-top:.7rem;color:var(--muted);font-size:.94rem;line-height:1.5;text-wrap:pretty;overflow:hidden;display:-webkit-box;-webkit-line-clamp:3;-webkit-box-orient:vertical">{s.summary}</p>
              <div style="margin-top:1.3rem;padding-top:.9rem;border-top:1px solid var(--line);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:.6rem;flex-wrap:wrap">
                <Publisher size={20} link={false} />
                <GateBadge compact={true} sealed={s.sealed} noun="seed" />
              </div>
            </a>
          ))}
        </div>
      ) : (
        <div style="margin-top:3.2rem;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:1rem;background:var(--card);padding:clamp(1.8rem,4vw,2.6rem)">
          <div style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:.5rem;color:var(--accent);font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',ui-monospace,monospace;font-size:.72rem;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;font-weight:600">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 22 22" width="16" height="16" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><circle cx="11" cy="11" r="4.2" fill="var(--accent)"></circle><circle cx="11" cy="2.6" r="1.5" fill="var(--accent)" opacity=".75"></circle><circle cx="18.6" cy="7.4" r="1.5" fill="var(--accent)" opacity=".55"></circle><circle cx="16.9" cy="16.9" r="1.5" fill="var(--accent)" opacity=".75"></circle><circle cx="5.1" cy="16.9" r="1.5" fill="var(--accent)" opacity=".55"></circle><circle cx="3.4" cy="7.4" r="1.5" fill="var(--accent)" opacity=".75"></circle></svg>
            the first seed is coming
          </div>
          <h2 style="margin-top:1rem;font-size:clamp(1.5rem,3.5vw,2.1rem);line-height:1.1;letter-spacing:-.03em;font-weight:720;max-width:22ch">No seeds published yet — here is what one will be.</h2>
          <p style="margin-top:1.1rem;max-width:60ch;color:var(--muted);font-size:1.02rem;line-height:1.6;text-wrap:pretty">A seed is a self-contained markdown file that teaches an agent in a repository that has never had a tool how to bring it in and stand it up: it <strong style="color:var(--ink)">detects</strong> whether the tool is already present, <strong style="color:var(--ink)">installs</strong> it from an origin the seed vouches for, <strong style="color:var(--ink)">proves</strong> the install took with a command it runs, <strong style="color:var(--ink)">uses</strong> it once for real, <strong style="color:var(--ink)">wires</strong> it into the repository's agent harness, and <strong style="color:var(--ink)">accounts</strong> for every move in a fixed report the human audits.</p>
          <p style="margin-top:1rem;max-width:60ch;color:var(--muted);font-size:1.02rem;line-height:1.6;text-wrap:pretty">Where a recipe's discipline is neutrality — it names no coordinate, so it transfers anywhere — a seed's is accountability for what it runs on your machine. Both are versioned and sealed, and both are read by an agent, not a person.</p>
          <div style="margin-top:1.8rem;display:flex;gap:1rem;flex-wrap:wrap;font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',ui-monospace,monospace;font-size:.82rem">
            <a href="what-is-a-seed.html" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:.4rem;color:var(--bg);background:var(--accent);border:1px solid var(--accent);border-radius:.55rem;padding:.5rem 1rem;text-decoration:none">What a seed is →</a>
            <a href="recipes.html" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:.4rem;color:var(--ink);background:var(--bg);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:.55rem;padding:.5rem 1rem;text-decoration:none">Browse the recipes →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      )}
    </section>
  </Frame>
</Layout>

<style>
  .seed-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--accent);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .seed-card {
      transition: none;
    }
    .seed-card:hover {
      transform: none;
    }
  }
</style>
